<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-90C8F720-CF47-4BFD-B0A4-AF5208D41820" version="2" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-90C8F720-CF47-4BFD-B0A4-AF5208D41820" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Instructions for safe use (Technician)</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M140666-B27" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">General safety warnings</title><p class="- topic/p ">We would like to draw your attention to the general warnings, summarized on this page. You will find specific warnings further on in the TSM in the descriptions of operations that have to be carried out in dangerous circumstances. 
</p><ul id="UL_2D17CF7E7E544CBAB54CE2F3BC3FDF38" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Before using compressed air, carefully read the instructions on the can and follow the instructions to avoid hazards. Always keep the can upright. Before cleaning, disconnect the power from the part to be cleaned. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Always look in the product safety guide and operation guide for additional safety information. 
</p></li><li id="LI_C5119AF57BA0441982595E6E8ABD5C13" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">AVOID DAMAGING PBA’S VIA ELECTROSTATIC DISCHARGES. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">You must wear the wristband, code number 7991.320 and use the antistatic mat, code number 7991.322. 
</p></li><li id="LI_9DD7AF4E107B4612A6316D8E9B1D4800" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">AVOID ELECTRIC SHOCKS! 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Switch off the power supply to the machine and remove the mains plug from the wall socket if the machine does not need to be on when you are working on it. 
</p></li><li id="LI_576776486F4A4ED2B01E15589D61DE87" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Power down: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Dis-connect the service jumper (22X6) during dis-assemblies</b> See: 
<xref keyref="22COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F9B91945-CB0C-4E4A-AFEB-0B62B0D1872C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 22 The components of Power?>22 The components of Power</xref> for the location
</p><fig id="FIG_807784338B2E41F9A834913CC06F286E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8DC62BCD-C522-4D57-9546-F89F95FEB348-low.png" id="IMAGE_BC14546C3E8F4BC2AFDC658925464919" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8DC62BCD-C522-4D57-9546-F89F95FEB348-low.png"/></fig></li><li id="LI_51BC07612C7344A899EE1EDED1CE7F26" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">AVOID MOVING PARTS! 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When you remove the panels from the machine, make sure that you do not get your fingers stuck between moving parts like chains, cogs and gear belts. 
</p></li><li id="LI_E69550746C7A4362BDC300CF2BC641FC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This equipment must be earthed. 
</p></li><li id="LI_38533E4DDCD94A59A5F41EBBDC71DCCC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This equipment is not suitable for connecting to an IT-power system, often used in stand-alone power systems (for example offshore, mining). When you are in doubt, consult your Technical Co-ordinator. 
</p></li><li id="LI_D076E084B1FF4140A441581DD2E10896" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure that the wall sockets and power switches are easily accessible. 
</p></li><li id="LI_216B50864505406294816067146C742E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A blown fuse does not guarantee a powerless situation. Replace a blown fuse only with correct type and rating. Overrule never the safety of a clixon. 
</p></li><li id="LI_0DCCC5644EEE40B48149DAF664A45AC0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If you must replace a power supply cable or power supply plug, only use components, which comply with the local regulations. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not use the print surface or top cover as a storage location. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-30CB28C0-AB4B-4F22-B1EE-3B3CA4CE5143" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">UVgel 460 ink</title><p class="- topic/p ">For detailed safety information regarding 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">UVgel 460 ink: See 
<xref keyref="EXTWICdocument001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-29569193-E31F-4297-919D-18E3155ADEA4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text WIC (Work Instruction Card) documents with safety information?>WIC (Work Instruction Card) documents with safety information</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-55C96FC5-FE98-4931-BC3A-595B5831F879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Cleaner D</title><p class="- topic/p ">For detailed safety information regarding Cleaner D (DMSO): See 
<xref keyref="EXTWICdocument001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-29569193-E31F-4297-919D-18E3155ADEA4.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text WIC (Work Instruction Card) documents with safety information?>WIC (Work Instruction Card) documents with safety information</xref>. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_15108A35214344C5968C619BBF8E9745" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">UV Light Safety</title><ul id="UL_0282C6A24E2A4667BAB89CA47AF912C8" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_48D62E927BF84EBEBC068B52823F6888" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Be aware that UV light is an invisible risk 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><note type="caution" id="GUID-49B362F8-7AA9-4630-A686-B17223F77B1E" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Keep the top cover closed and place all top covers on the printer when operating the UV curing lamps 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_1767C5F2C4194F56B8DD0F2146B83153" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Some medications can make you more susceptible to UV light 
</p></li><li id="LI_6E3FC3BBE1014C0089D09F3832AFD02E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Wear appropriate clothing that protects the skin from UV light exposure 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="SECTION_399AC2C0476F49069133BA10B594F827" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Safety information</title><p class="- topic/p ">The latest Product Safety Data Sheet (PSDS) and Material Safety Data Sheets (MSDS) for this system are available on http://downloads.cpp.canon. 
</p></section><section id="M140666-B28" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Safety interlock test</title><p class="- topic/p ">After every service visit you must do a safety interlock test. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The purpose of the test is to check that the customer cannot make a copy when a cover, panel or door is open. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Follow the instructions below. 
</p><ol id="OL_ADD6E3AA951A4CC696593AE8C8AF7028" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_FA5563954B8C49A6AA5658522D5F0B91" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Switch ON the Print Engine. 
</p></li><li id="LI_3C8A6D367DDF49C3A576B637E34B0DE7" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Make a copy to check that the Print Engine operates correctly. 
</p></li><li id="LI_BBF47C8443724E689493872AAF588E71" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Open one cover, panel or door to activate a safety interlock switch. 
</p></li><li id="LI_B84412F700884D669821723681278588" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check that you cannot make a copy / print. 
</p></li><li id="LI_C964199C9F60404C83B68739B3639077" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Close the cover, panel or door and open another cover, panel or door. 
</p></li><li id="LI_A71D433EC5F04F9E92DCDD539478EDB9" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Check that you cannot make a copy / print. 
</p></li><li id="LI_0E12388C508545B8B60EE3ACE35EABD0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Continue until you checked all safety interlock switches. 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="M140666-B29" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional test</title><p class="- topic/p ">After every service visit a functional test must be done. The customer must agree that the machine or product performs according to his expectations and within the machine specifications written down in this Technical Service Manual. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-51D60043-A562-4957-8F25-54813DE8FAAC" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The following indicators are used in the documentation to identify and categorize the level of the seriousness of hazard</title><table id="GUID-A8A82525-168F-4BC2-A7F6-1603AB0C8461" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="65*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Symbol 
